Quote:  N.Z. Grapefruit Wrongly Named [heading] The export potential of New Zealand grapefruit could be enhanced if it was renamed, delegates to the annual conference of the New Zealand Citrus and Sub-tropical Council have been told. ... New Zealand grapefruit are not, in fact grapefruit at all. They are a type of orangelo, and probably more accurately described by the nickname `poor man's orange.'
